rComments: I absolutely loved this course and her! She is engaging, the material is eye opening, and I would recommend this course to anyone in a psych major. Know the material in the lectures inside out, and do all of the readings. The terminology can get tricky just because it is so similar, but if you know the material well, you're golden.

Speaks in a patronizing tone, but definitely an easy mark. Could be enjoyable but she messily throws slides together, and glosses over important world issues to repeat word for word what the textbook says.

If you played a text to voice program, and ran the textbook over the slides and textbook, you would basically have this course. No depth, doesn't challenge critical thinking, spoon feeds you what is correct. No learning, only regurgitation unfortunately.

she makes the content very interesting and she gives lots of examples from her experience as a clinical psychologist which really helps add context. Her lecture slides are very informative and easy to understand which makes it easy to follow her during the lecture. she has such a nice/caring/easy going energy and engages in lots of discussions!

Had her for both PSYB30 and PSYC12. Her lectures are engaging (they aren't boring and the material isn't dry). She's very accessible and extremely fair in terms of assessment. Pay attention to the small details in the lecture. Great prof.

Shona's a great prof, and she really is passionate about what she teaches. She's very nice and approachable. Lectures were super interesting and there's so many things you can take away from the course that has real life applications
Memorize all the readings, even the small details or you won't do well. But she is a very interesting professor and I would take her course again
teacherRatingTags: ['Lots of homework', "Skip class? You won't pass."]

rComments: If you know the lectures in and out you'll be fine. Readings seem like a lot but most is repetition of the studies from the lecture. The readings are a small amount of the testable content. The tests are fair, it is unlikely for you to do poorly if you read the material. Read the material, get a 4.0.
